com.gemalto.idp.mobile.authentication.mode.face

Interface FaceAuthVerifierCallback


  • public interface FaceAuthVerifierCallback
    Face Auth Mode enrollment completed (either success or failure) handler. One of the method is always called so that the UI code does not have to implement any timeout upon it.
    Since:
    4.2

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onVerifyError(IdpException e)
      This callback function is called if the face is not correctly configured or an internal cryptographic error occurs.
      void onVerifyFail(FaceAuthStatus status)
      This callback function is called if FaceAuthVerifier.authenticateUser(int, Authenticatable, FaceAuthVerifierCallback) fails.
      void onVerifyFinish(FaceAuthInput faceAuthInput)
      It is called as soon as the verification process completes.

    • Method Detail

      • onVerifyFinish

        void onVerifyFinish(FaceAuthInput faceAuthInput)
        It is called as soon as the verification process completes.

        It is guaranteed that:

        • This method is called on the main UI thread, so that the UI code can directly act on it.
        • This method is never called from within the context of the verifier method - i.e. always after the FaceAuthVerifier.authenticateUser(int, Authenticatable, FaceAuthVerifierCallback) method returns.
        Parameters:
        faceAuthInput - represents the authenticated face authentication input object.

      • onVerifyFail

        void onVerifyFail(FaceAuthStatus status)
        This callback function is called if FaceAuthVerifier.authenticateUser(int, Authenticatable, FaceAuthVerifierCallback) fails.
        Parameters:
        status - the face authentication result.

      • onVerifyError

        void onVerifyError(IdpException e)
        This callback function is called if the face is not correctly configured or an internal cryptographic error occurs.
        Parameters:
        e - exception object indicating problem.
